issue.title: first commit bricktunes code
issue.body: first commit bricktunes LEGO color synth glove. The `cedargrove_chime` library is in the community bundle, but i think it has a path typo (`liibraries`) at the moment, so not sure if that'll cause any issues. I've let @CedarGroveStudios know about the issue.

comment.body:
The Chime library depends on another Community Bundle library, cedargrove_midi_tools. Unfortunately, it appears that circup only recognizes dependencies with `adafruit_...` libraries and core modules listed in `requirements.txt`. I've filed an issue https://github.com/adafruit/CircuitPython_Community_Bundle/issues/192 with the Community Bundle repo and will follow-up with an issue for circup 
In the mean time, the Learning Guide should note that the cedargrove_midi_tools library (available in the bundle and installable with circup) is required.
